    <h1>Evacuation Map Guide</h1>
    <p>Learn How to Safely Exit Buildings During Emergencies</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Understand the Map</h2>
    <p>Every building has an evacuation map displayed on walls. Learn to identify:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Primary exit routes</li>
      <li>Secondary (alternative) routes</li>
      <li>Fire extinguishers & alarm locations</li>
      <li>Assembly points</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Follow Exit Signs</h2>
    <p>During emergencies, always follow the green exit signs that guide towards safety.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Safe Practices During Evacuation</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Walk quickly but don’t run</li>
      <li>Stay in line and don’t push others</li>
      <li>Assist younger children and elderly</li>
      <li>Keep emergency kit with you if possible</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Assembly Point</h2>
    <p>All students and staff should assemble at the pre-decided safe area outside the building. Teachers will take attendance.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Do Not Re-enter</h2>
    <p>Never go back inside the building until it has been declared safe by the authorities.</p>
  </section>

